Accenture Data Analysis and Visualization Internship
📊 Data-Driven Insights for Business Strategy

Overview
This repository contains my work from the Accenture Data Analytics and Visualization Virtual Internship, where I analyzed business data to extract insights and provide recommendations.

Project Workflow
1️⃣ Understanding the Problem
Defined key business questions to analyze.
Focused on identifying top-performing content categories and engagement trends.
2️⃣ Data Collection & Preparation
Selected 3 relevant datasets out of 7 provided.
Cleaned and preprocessed the data (handled missing values, removed duplicates, and standardized formats).
Merged the datasets for a comprehensive analysis.
3️⃣ Data Analysis & Insights
Identified top 5 content categories with the highest engagement.
Analyzed content type performance (photos, videos, etc.).
Found the month with the highest number of posts.
4️⃣ Data Visualization
Created bar charts, line graphs, and heatmaps to showcase insights.
5️⃣ Summary Report & Recommendations
Compiled key findings into a structured report.
Provided data-driven recommendations for content strategy improvements.
6️⃣ Final Presentation
Presented insights and recommendations to the team & client.
Skills & Tools Used
✅ Python (Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
✅ Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
✅ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
✅ Data Visualization & Reporting

Key Findings & Recommendations
📌 Top Categories: Animal, Science, Healthy Eating, Technology, and Food.
📌 Best Performing Content Type: Photos and videos had the highest engagement.
📌 Peak Posting Month: May had the most content published.
📌 Recommendation: Focus on top categories and content types for higher engagement.

Repository Structure
📂 README/
📂 Data/ → Raw & cleaned datasets
📂 Notebooks/ → Jupyter notebooks with analysis and Visualizations
📂 Presentation/

Conclusion
This project helped me apply data analysis techniques in a business setting, improving my skills in problem-solving, data visualization, and decision-making.
